         <abstract>
            <p>The Fǝkkāre malakot is a theological treatise transmitted in the codex unicus <ref type="mss" corresp="BNFet119"/>
            together with <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1578hamara"/>, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1885Marsam"/> and <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2635Dawana"/>. 
            It deals with the weakness of
         human understanding regarding the mystery of the Godhead and had been attributed to the za-Mikāʾelites, but is now considered to be the work of an Ethiopian Orthodox monophysite
         monastic milieu.</p>
            <p>
